com.misc.common.moplaf.dbsynch

Interface DbSynchUnitAbstract

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataSource, DataSourceJdbc, DbSynchUnit
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataSourceImpl, DataSourceJdbcImpl, DbSynchUnitAbstractImpl, DbSynchUnitImpl

    public interface DbSynchUnitAbstract
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'DbSynchUnit Abstract'.

    A DbSynch unit is the unit of synchronization. It supports

    • down synchronization: database date synchronized from the object data,
    • up synchronization: object data synchronized from database data.

    A DbSynch contains Table's and child units.

    Specializations of DbSynch provide parameter values, that are gotten via getParamValue(EAttribute).

    The following features are supported:

    • Tables
    • Data Source
    • Name
    • Child Units
    See Also:
    DbSynchPackage.getDbSynchUnitAbstract()
